column394: Complete overview of project specifications, photos and notes with foreman assigned to job prior to commencement. Specifications are for the replacement of Flat roof sections: Evaluate premises for optimal landscaping protection. Set up a jobsite staging area for debris removal. Caution tape will be displayed around dump truck for safety. Set up jobsite safety equipment on roof necessary to adhere to all OSHA requirements and regulations. Safety harnesses and ropes will be utilized. Tear off existing layer(s) of roofing down to the roof deck. Remove and dispose of old roofing material in sections and ensure roof is waterproof overnight. Core test must be completed before installation to investigate substrate to determine if new installation will be fastened or Fully Adhered, using Installation best application. Inspect existing wood deck and inspect framing condition and advise property owner(s) of necessary/recommended repair at additional costs of per sheet of CDX and $95.00 per hour for any framing repairs. Plank board will be replaced at (1x6 -$6/foot) (1x8 - $8/foot) (1x10 - $10/foot & 2x4 - $4/foot) (2x6 - $6/foot) (2x8 - $8/foot) (2x10 - $10/foot)Install new insulation panels fastened using drill point insulation fasteners and 3 plates over roof deck.(16 plates & screws will be used per 4x8 board)Install new 0.60: 0.80: TPO: PVC: Membrane Fully Adhered flat roof system. Install new preformed vent boot where applicable. Install new 1 termination bars along wall intersection. Terminate membrane wall/curb flashing with termination bar detail along wall intersections. Install new pre-manufactured Scuppers & Drains and continuous perimeter heat welded lap. Install new custom-bent 0.32: 0.14: aluminum flashing around perimeter of roof in applicable places. Install new parapet wall caps around perimeter of the roof in applicable places. Caulk and seal all flashings. Paint plumbing stacks. Run magnet over premises to pick up loose nails. Clean premises; haul away all job-related debris. NOTE Magnet will be continuous. A Certified inspector will inspect the entire job before, during & after completion to ensure all work is performed according to contract. The price does not include wood replacement unless otherwise noted. We will install custom made parapet wall to create a true separation between the flat roof were replacing and the neighbor's flat roof.

This project will involve replacing the bitumen-type roof on the step-down roof at back of the house.  The new roof will be a white, .08-inch, thermoplastic polyolefin (TPO) membrane installed over 1/2 inch compressed ISO-board insulation, which shall be attached to the wood deck original to this 1887 rowhouse.  The wood deck is in good shape, and we do not anticipate the need to replace any wood. Contractor will also install TPO flashings and/or metal counter flashings, as required by manufacturer, to all curbs, walls, and penetrations.  Contractor will install aluminum drip edges with 5.5 inch flashings, which shall be sealed in accordance with manufacturer specifications.Contractor will install TPO pipe vent covers
